uestions\", \"from\": 3351, \"to\": 3360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why have the IOC's statements been so misleading and nebulous?\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3411, \"end\": 3414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0715462453697229e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps because it does not want to compromise the athletes' privacy by discussing their medical details without consent.\", \"from\": 3461, \"to\": 3582, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes' privacy\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"their medical details\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3565}, {\"ngram\": \"consent\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3581}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And perhaps because the IOC's leaders are not prepared to defend their own rules, which state that even if Lin and Khelif do have XY chromosomes, they are allowed to compete in Olympic women's boxing.\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3607, \"end\": 3610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0715462453697229e-49, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3713, \"end\": 3727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their own rules\", \"f